cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper discusses information security measures in wireless ad hoc and mobile networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on physical layer security framework and signal processing algorithms, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of cooperative group key generation also involves system and control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the study investigates the application of the proposed protocol to Impulse Radio - Ultra Wideband (IR-UWB) channels, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) as IR-UWB is often used for high-speed data transfer in multimedia applications.
